For decades now The Tower‚Äôs phallic nature has been the butt of many jokes  and taking a picture from a low angle to add to the obscene nature of the image has been much to the amusement of countless freshmen and to the chagrin of the UT administration.  At The University of Texas at Austin  our reputation is of the utmost importance. It is unacceptable to receive constant complaints of the suggestive nature of the arrangement of The Tower and the metal spheres being intentional.  President Fenves and the UT Board of Regents has been weighing all possible remedies to this situation. As The Tower is an iconic landmark for the university and city  and the metal spheres cannot be removed as part of the deal with the artist  the arrangement cannot be changed. Thus we came to the conclusion that the only possible solution was to add a diagram of the female reproductive system to the renovations at Darrell K. Royal-Texas Memorial Stadium.
